The National Commission for Refugees, Migrants and Internally Displaced Persons (NCFRM) in synergy with the Kaduna State Emergency Management Agency (KADSEMA),  have flagged off the distribution of relief materials to the internally displaced persons in Kajuru Local Government Area, as a result of Herders attacks. Speaking at the official flag off of the items, the Executive Secretary of KADSEMA, Hon. Maimunatu Asabe Abubakar, showed gratitude for el’Rufai’s compassion for the well-being of victims of incessant attacks and killings by the criminal elements across the state. She commended the representative of NCFRM for their efforts in alleviating the suffering of the victims. The ES further advised the victims of the attacks, to make judicious use of the items and not to sell them for financial exchange, as the government would not tolerate such from any quarter. Hon. Maimunatu also called on the people of the area to be on alert at all times and report suspected persons encroaching into their territory. The ES-KADSEMA, added that the government at all levels is penetrating all IDP camps, in all the affected areas in the state, to identify and alleviate their suffering, by providing succour to them. The Federal Commissioner of the Commission Sen. Sani Bashir Mohammed, who was ably represented by the Admin officer, Mrs. Aisha Mohammed, said the gesture was informed by the kindheartedness and human sympathy of the commissioner. She applauded the ES-Kadsema and the state government for their unrelenting efforts, in cushioning the hardship of the displaced persons. LEADERSHIP reports that the Items distributed includes: Wrappers, women gowns, Male wears, soap, detergents, cooking pots, ceramic plates, plastic cups, buckets, spoons, treated mosquito nets, blankets and nylon mats.